What is the total number of books read by all four friends?', '{"A": "15", "B": "17", "C": "19", "D": "21"}', 'B', 'Add all the numbers: 5 + 3 + 7 + 2 = 17. The distractors include 15 (missing one friend), 19 (adding an extra book), and 21 (double-counting).'),
	('04de449c-1dee-49f1-b396-a08ccf70547e', '6521b4af-de4e-4a3d-a67e-b9ae8ad93277', 'high_school_adaptive_core_d1_spatial_reasoning_1768625391248_vlimp9', 'C', true, 2409, 1, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 14, '2026-01-27 06:48:39.039411+00', 'Which shape will complete the pattern? The sequence shows: Square, Circle, Triangle, Square, Circle, ________.', '{"A": "Square", "B": "Circle", "C": "Triangle", "D": "Rectangle"}', 'C', 'The pattern repeats every three shapes: Square, Circle, Triangle. The next shape should be Triangle.'),
	('c38e910e-d51c-4a18-b780-a81a0fbb9150', '6521b4af-de4e-4a3d-a67e-b9ae8ad93277', 'high_school_adaptive_core_d1_numerical_reasoning_1768625391248_35c054', 'D', false, 1821, 1, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 16, '2026-01-27 06:48:49.091174+00', 'If a car travels at 60 km/h for 2.5 hours, how far does it travel?', '{"A": "120 km", "B": "150 km", "C": "180 km", "D": "200 km"}', 'B', 'Distance = Speed × Time = 60 km/h × 2.5 hours = 150 km.'),
