	('c465ecf6-9ff5-467d-b049-ba24162cedae', 'd0f35510-1e79-4bee-8b0e-b581f62bf9ae', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d4_logical_reasoning_1769755130611_l6b274', 'C', true, 2073, 4, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 17, '2026-02-02 05:39:29.476476+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, and 25 books are placed on it, which of the following statements is true?', '{"A": "The bookshelf is half full", "B": "The bookshelf is a quarter full", "C": "The bookshelf is more than half full but not full", "D": "The bookshelf is completely full"}', 'C', 'The bookshelf can hold 5 * 8 = 40 books. With 25 books, it is more than half full (20 books would be half) but not completely full.'),
