	('b1d6420c-10da-4e92-b670-f80945b846de', '9861d060-4fe8-4e5d-8fb6-085e651961b5', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_spatial_reasoning_1769754696932_2qnwqv', 'D', true, 8606, 3, 'spatial_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 6, '2026-02-02 10:27:59.414243+00', 'Imagine a cube with each side being 6 units long. What is the volume of this cube?', '{"A": "60 cubic units", "B": "120 cubic units", "C": "180 cubic units", "D": "216 cubic units"}', 'D', 'The volume of a cube is calculated by cubing the length of one side: 6^3 = 216 cubic units'),
