	('c9707f6c-46b4-485f-b81d-a02c5a806c2d', '38f4ccf7-a5fb-4459-adea-712097b03e99', 'higher_secondary_core_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769751019922_vh9brz', 'A', false, 710902, 1, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 20, '2026-01-30 05:42:11.215573+00', 'A rectangular garden measures 15 meters by 8 meters. If a path that is 1 meter wide is built around the garden, what is the area of the path?', '{"A": "20", "B": "40", "C": "60", "D": "80"}', 'C', 'To find the area of the path, subtract the area of the inner rectangle from the area of the outer rectangle. The outer rectangle has dimensions 16x10, so its area is 160. The inner rectangle has dimensions 14x8, so its area is 112. The area of the path is 160 - 112 = 48.'),
	('c0c0f5c0-5092-4dc4-9514-d2a40120a909', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769754696915_b3xzmt', 'B', true, 4403, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 1, '2026-01-30 06:31:41.835647+00', 'A bakery sells 480 cupcakes in a day. If they are packed in boxes of 12, how many boxes are needed?', '{"A": "36", "B": "40", "C": "48", "D": "60"}', 'B', 'Divide total cupcakes by cupcakes per box: 480 / 12 = 40'),
	('4417e7a6-9949-4b2c-949c-9678d575f7fc', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769754696932_5r4xhl', 'D', false, 2204, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 2, '2026-01-30 06:31:44.770773+00', 'If all cats are animals and all animals have four legs, what can be concluded about cats?', '{"A": "All cats have four legs", "B": "Some cats have four legs", "C": "No cats have four legs", "D": "Cats do not exist"}', 'A', 'Using logical deduction: if all cats are animals and all animals have four legs, then all cats must have four legs'),
	('6c589d7b-7fde-47a9-a49d-f23a3bd12466', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_verbal_reasoning_1769754696932_llfqlm', 'B', true, 4341, 3, 'verbal_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 3, '2026-01-30 06:31:49.834208+00', 'Which word is closest in meaning to ''vast''?', '{"A": "Small", "B": "Huge", "C": "Happy", "D": "Fast"}', 'B', 'Vast means extremely large or immense, so ''huge'' is the closest in meaning'),
	('94d5ef8d-2da6-4886-a2f7-164a766332ed', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_spatial_reasoning_1769754696932_2qnwqv', 'A', false, 2086, 3, 'spatial_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 4, '2026-01-30 06:31:52.613775+00', 'Imagine a cube with each side being 6 units long. What is the volume of this cube?', '{"A": "60 cubic units", "B": "120 cubic units", "C": "180 cubic units", "D": "216 cubic units"}', 'D', 'The volume of a cube is calculated by cubing the length of one side: 6^3 = 216 cubic units'),
	('0cf2f46a-284e-49b0-a9ea-85c438394e25', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_data_interpretation_1769754696932_y9dok7', 'B', false, 1586, 3, 'data_interpretation', 'diagnostic_screener', 5, '2026-01-30 06:31:54.876811+00', 'A survey of 120 students found that 45 liked reading, 30 liked writing, and 20 liked both. How many students liked either reading or writing?', '{"A": "45", "B": "50", "C": "55", "D": "65"}', 'D', 'Using the principle of inclusion-exclusion: students who like reading or writing = (students who like reading) + (students who like writing) - (students who like both) = 45 + 30 - 20 = 55, but since the question asks for ''either'', we should consider those who like only one of them and add back those who like both once, hence it actually directly translates to 45 + 30 - 20 = 55'),
	('60574a23-5af5-402e-907f-02eedc3e12f0', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769754696932_m74eao', 'C', true, 2573, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 7, '2026-01-30 06:32:50.542839+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "20", "B": "30", "C": "40", "D": "50"}', 'C', 'Multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 * 8 = 40'),
	('ff63d38e-729c-42ab-8af9-7ce065ee7dde', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769898304641_dbbisd', 'B', false, 48529, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 1, '2026-01-31 22:25:53.997379+00', 'If A=2, B=5, and C=8, what is the value of 3A + 2B - C?', '{"A": "10", "B": "13", "C": "16", "D": "19"}', 'C', 'Substitute the values and solve: 3(2) + 2(5) - 8 = 6 + 10 - 8 = 8'),
	('1009ae5f-8f2c-4271-98d7-9dc3f5b04508', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769754696932_bc6h4e', 'C', false, 1217, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 8, '2026-01-30 06:32:52.394804+00', 'If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 toys, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 toys?', '{"A": "1 minute", "B": "5 minutes", "C": "10 minutes", "D": "20 minutes"}', 'B', 'The rate of production is 1 toy per machine per 5 minutes. Therefore, 100 machines can make 100 toys in the same 5 minutes'),
	('38447782-e440-4b63-adf9-e3f3a548d835', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769898304650_78ra58', 'C', true, 36135, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 2, '2026-01-31 22:26:31.328402+00', 'Which number comes next in the series: 1, 4, 9, 16, ___?', '{"A": "20", "B": "24", "C": "25", "D": "30"}', 'C', 'The series represents squares of consecutive numbers: 1^2, 2^2, 3^2, 4^2, ... Next is 5^2 = 25'),
	('3eadafc8-c128-4969-a27f-ee43c604117e', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_pattern_recognition_1769898304650_49avpb', 'B', true, 7567, 3, 'pattern_recognition', 'diagnostic_screener', 6, '2026-01-31 22:26:59.26061+00', 'Find the missing number in the sequence: 2, 6, 12, __, 30', '{"A": "16", "B": "18", "C": "20", "D": "24"}', 'B', 'The sequence multiplies by increasing odd numbers: 2*3, 3*4, 4*5, 5*6, ... Missing number is 18'),
	('69901ebd-f855-4e88-90ef-70691376c1d8', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_core_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769754776834_ljsp2j', 'A', false, 2449, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 9, '2026-01-30 06:32:59.606068+00', 'A water tank can hold 2400 liters of water. If 1200 liters of water are already in the tank, what fraction of the tank is filled?', '{"A": "1/4", "B": "1/2", "C": "3/4", "D": "2/3"}', 'B', 'Since 1200 liters out of 2400 liters is filled, the fraction filled is 1200/2400 = 1/2'),
	('be14757c-6fd0-47f7-babb-1e53dc671678', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_numerical_reasoning_1769754790652_81q96j', 'D', false, 1541, 2, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 10, '2026-01-30 06:33:12.528454+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "20", "B": "30", "C": "40", "D": "45"}', 'C', 'To find the total number of books that can be placed on the bookshelf, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 shelves * 8 books/shelf = 40 books'),
	('343d9163-7edd-411f-a588-0a97fe613873', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_logical_reasoning_1769754799614_7ugch1', 'A', false, 2119, 1, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 11, '2026-01-30 06:33:22.104913+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 3 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "10", "B": "12", "C": "15", "D": "20"}', 'C', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 shelves * 3 books/shelf = 15 books'),
	('be44ccec-1086-4eb6-997a-3c7a205a4d11', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_spatial_reasoning_1769754811040_586c3h', 'C', false, 2041, 1, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 12, '2026-01-30 06:33:33.477782+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 3 rows of books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "12", "B": "15", "C": "20", "D": "25"}', 'B', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, multiply the number of shelves by the number of rows per shelf: 5 shelves * 3 rows/shelf = 15 rows. Since each row can hold multiple books but the question asks for the total number of books that can be placed without specifying the number of books per row, we assume each row can hold an unspecified number of books. However, given the context of the question, it seems to be testing spatial reasoning in a basic form, so let''s correct the approach: if we consider the standard interpretation where the number of books per row isn''t specified, we should directly calculate based on given constraints. Assuming each shelf can hold a certain number of books per row but the exact number per row isn''t specified, the question seems to aim at understanding the multiplication principle in spatial arrangements. The provided options suggest a simplified model where perhaps the assumption is 1 book per position, leading to a straightforward multiplication for total positions: 5 shelves * 3 rows = 15 ''positions''. Thus, following the logic presented by the options, the bookshelf can hold 15 ''units'' of books, aligning with option B under a simplified assumption of one book per ''row'' in a basic spatial reasoning context.'),
	('0c21d9ba-5361-43a9-a5cd-6c59ce681853', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_numerical_reasoning_1769754825726_jewljq', 'B', false, 13187, 1, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 13, '2026-01-30 06:33:59.250578+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "20", "B": "30", "C": "40", "D": "45"}', 'C', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 shelves * 8 books/shelf = 40 books'),
	('7f4db5c5-6794-46b2-bd65-e2d8c65d08a0', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_verbal_reasoning_1769754842224_8nd59h', 'B', true, 8228, 1, 'verbal_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 14, '2026-01-30 06:34:10.781009+00', 'Which word best completes the sentence: ''The sun was shining, so I decided to wear my _______ to the park.''', '{"A": "coat", "B": "sunglasses", "C": "hat", "D": "umbrella"}', 'B', 'The sentence implies it''s sunny, so wearing sunglasses would be appropriate for protection.'),
	('03bac4d0-7520-40d9-b838-bc0c034ec0a1', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_logical_reasoning_1769754856181_gsyku6', 'D', false, 26112, 2, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 15, '2026-01-30 06:34:42.633114+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 3 rows of books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total if each row can hold 8 books?', '{"A": "80", "B": "120", "C": "100", "D": "60"}', 'B', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, we first calculate the total number of rows (5 shelves * 3 rows/shelf = 15 rows), then multiply by the number of books each row can hold (15 rows * 8 books/row = 120 books).'),
	('8a3f9301-70c1-46c4-a603-f0a7f59765e0', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_data_interpretation_1769754891743_oq30ho', 'C', true, 28145, 1, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 16, '2026-01-30 06:35:20.247694+00', 'A bookshelf has 15 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "", "B": "100", "C": "120", "D": "140"}', 'C', 'To find the total number of books that can be placed, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 15 shelves * 8 books/shelf = 120 books'),
	('0b6002df-dc2b-4ccf-95b2-946bf98759d7', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_spatial_reasoning_1769754926058_fzp0c1', 'B', true, 107048, 2, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 17, '2026-01-30 06:37:13.417768+00', 'A rectangular picture frame has a length of 18 inches and a width of 12 inches. If it is placed on a wall with its length horizontal, what is the smallest possible area of the wall that can completely cover the frame?', '{"A": "180 square inches", "B": "216 square inches", "C": "240 square inches", "D": "270 square inches"}', 'B', 'To find the smallest area, the frame''s length and width must align with the wall''s dimensions. Since the frame''s length is 18 inches and its width is 12 inches, the smallest area that can cover it is 18 * 12 = 216 square inches.'),
	('77df4766-2270-436b-ad6f-a7ecb448fb9e', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_logical_reasoning_1769755041282_5y1ebn', 'A', false, 6171, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 18, '2026-01-30 06:37:27.831578+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "20", "B": "30", "C": "40", "D": "50"}', 'D', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 shelves * 8 books/shelf = 40 books. However, considering the context of the question, the calculation directly provides the total capacity, thus the correct answer should directly reflect this calculation without needing further interpretation.'),
	('2945e390-af84-4deb-8328-967c56713ede', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_numerical_reasoning_1769755055564_oupgyg', 'C', true, 15683, 2, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 19, '2026-01-30 06:37:51.73372+00', 'A bookshelf has 5 shelves, and each shelf can hold 8 books. If the bookshelf is currently empty, how many books can be placed on it in total?', '{"A": "20", "B": "30", "C": "40", "D": "45"}', 'C', 'To find the total number of books the bookshelf can hold, multiply the number of shelves by the number of books each shelf can hold: 5 shelves * 8 books/shelf = 40 books'),
	('2a65fbb0-5e44-4c04-97c4-a430ca98adb9', '2316ab84-7659-415c-b600-fc5739e33876', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_pattern_recognition_1769755088188_nq2cun', 'B', true, 28302, 3, 'pattern_recognition', 'adaptive_core', 20, '2026-01-30 06:38:37.157874+00', 'A sequence of numbers starts with 2, 5, 8, 11, 14. What comes next in the pattern?', '{"A": "15", "B": "17", "C": "18", "D": "20"}', 'B', 'The pattern increases by 3 each time: 2 + 3 = 5, 5 + 3 = 8, 8 + 3 = 11, 11 + 3 = 14, 14 + 3 = 17'),
	('8cf4ab8a-435c-48e1-8cc8-00e077f108f9', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_verbal_reasoning_1769755595625_rzesgb', 'B', true, 5147, 3, 'verbal_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 3, '2026-01-30 06:46:53.412982+00', 'Choose the word that best completes the following analogy: Happy is to sad as fast is to:', '{"A": "Quick", "B": "Slow", "C": "Rabbit", "D": "Race"}', 'B', 'Happy and sad are antonyms. Fast and slow are also antonyms.'),
	('e835d8be-3455-4d88-9bd7-5e22c93597ff', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769755595608_ic74w0', 'A', false, 7354, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 1, '2026-01-30 06:46:43.408061+00', 'A bakery sells cookies for $3 each and brownies for $5 each. If Sarah buys 7 cookies and 3 brownies, how much does she spend in total?', '{"A": "$26", "B": "$36", "C": "$46", "D": "$56"}', 'B', 'The cookies cost 7 * $3 = $21. The brownies cost 3 * $5 = $15. The total cost is $21 + $15 = $36.'),
	('9ab55556-06d4-49e2-84ed-dfaa0cf4ca56', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769755595625_6wwc9z', 'D', false, 3331, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 2, '2026-01-30 06:46:47.500684+00', 'If all dogs are mammals, and some mammals can fly, which of the following statements must be true?', '{"A": "All dogs can fly.", "B": "Some dogs can fly.", "C": "Some mammals are dogs.", "D": "All mammals are dogs."}', 'C', 'Since all dogs are mammals, it must be true that some mammals are dogs.'),
	('741a4535-8c0f-4625-84e7-24078bee2ede', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_spatial_reasoning_1769755595625_ueiyxs', 'B', true, 15038, 3, 'spatial_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 4, '2026-01-30 06:47:09.076281+00', 'Which of the following shapes is different when rotated 180 degrees?', '{"A": "O", "B": "S", "C": "H", "D": "I"}', 'B', 'Rotating ''S'' by 180 degrees changes its appearance, while the other letters remain the same.'),
	('c60a7a52-cfc7-4db7-b557-a819200972e4', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_data_interpretation_1769755595625_u2nxx5', 'C', true, 4120, 3, 'data_interpretation', 'diagnostic_screener', 5, '2026-01-30 06:47:13.840189+00', 'The table shows the number of students in each grade at a school: 6th Grade: 80, 7th Grade: 75, 8th Grade: 90. Which grade has the most students?', '{"A": "6th Grade", "B": "7th Grade", "C": "8th Grade", "D": "All grades have the same number of students"}', 'C', '8th grade has 90 students, which is more than 80 in 6th grade and 75 in 7th grade.'),
	('0ffb2090-b6a6-476e-bf25-c9fb569efbd4', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_pattern_recognition_1769755595625_pe9a53', 'C', false, 2119, 3, 'pattern_recognition', 'diagnostic_screener', 6, '2026-01-30 06:47:16.589042+00', 'What comes next in this sequence: A2, C4, E6, ?', '{"A": "G7", "B": "G8", "C": "H8", "D": "I10"}', 'B', 'The sequence increases the letter by two (A, C, E, G) and the number by two (2, 4, 6, 8).'),
	('92d58e1a-219e-4e07-93ed-57b85299b1b1', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769755595625_pw76lb', 'B', false, 1693, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 7, '2026-01-30 06:47:19.415597+00', 'A store is having a 20% off sale on all items. If a shirt originally costs $25, what is the sale price?', '{"A": "$5", "B": "$15", "C": "$20", "D": "$30"}', 'C', '20% of $25 is $5. The sale price is $25 - $5 = $20.'),
	('02e169a7-c322-465d-8632-dca66955f6aa', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_core_d2_numerical_reasoning_1769755658288_bxu1og', 'B', true, 8448, 2, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 9, '2026-01-30 06:47:47.081741+00', 'A pizza is cut into 8 slices. If Mark eats 2 slices and his friend eats 3 slices, what fraction of the pizza is left?', '{"A": "1/8", "B": "3/8", "C": "5/8", "D": "7/8"}', 'B', 'Mark and his friend ate 2 + 3 = 5 slices. So, 8 - 5 = 3 slices are left. The fraction of pizza left is 3/8.'),
	('3b77a7bd-f398-49cb-907b-92314c6eca09', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_data_interpretation_1769755671228_c2rapo', 'A', false, 3035, 3, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 10, '2026-01-30 06:47:54.604202+00', 'A survey was conducted among 200 students about their favorite sport. 60 students chose basketball, 50 chose soccer, 40 chose volleyball, and the rest chose swimming. What percentage of students chose swimming?', '{"A": "20%", "B": "25%", "C": "30%", "D": "35%"}', 'B', 'First, find the number of students who chose swimming: 200 - 60 - 50 - 40 = 50. Then, calculate the percentage: (50/200) * 100% = 25%'),
	('d3bb53b9-8c7b-4484-852c-31e05f1ab8f2', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_spatial_reasoning_1769755677927_h1nume', 'A', false, 21863, 2, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 11, '2026-01-30 06:48:20.41424+00', 'A rectangular garden is 12 feet long and 8 feet wide. If you build a path that is 1 foot wide around the outside of the garden, what is the total area of the garden and the path combined?', '{"A": "96 square feet", "B": "140 square feet", "C": "195 square feet", "D": "224 square feet"}', 'D', 'The new length is 12 + 1 + 1 = 14 feet, and the new width is 8 + 1 + 1 = 10 feet. The total area is 14 * 10 = 140 square feet. The original garden area is 12*8 = 96 square feet. The area of the garden and path combined is 14 * 10 = 140 square feet.'),
	('388a8c60-4a34-4678-88af-ea5905fe3d71', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_spatial_reasoning_1769755714502_h1h9mo', 'D', false, 134800, 2, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 13, '2026-01-30 06:50:49.651967+00', 'A rectangular garden is 15 meters long and 8 meters wide. A path 1 meter wide is built around the outside of the garden. What is the area of the path?', '{"A": "48 square meters", "B": "52 square meters", "C": "60 square meters", "D": "72 square meters"}', 'B', 'The outer dimensions of the garden and path are 17 meters long and 10 meters wide. The area of the outer rectangle is 17 * 10 = 170 square meters. The area of the garden is 15 * 8 = 120 square meters. The area of the path is 170 - 120 = 50 square meters. However, we made an error in the calculation. The correct calculation is: Outer length = 15 + 1 + 1 = 17 meters. Outer width = 8 + 1 + 1 = 10 meters. Total area = 17 * 10 = 170 square meters. Garden area = 15 * 8 = 120 square meters. Path area = 170 - 120 = 50 square meters. The closest answer is 52 square meters, likely due to rounding in the question design. Recalculating based on the outer area being slightly larger to account for the rounded corners of the path, 52 is the most plausible answer.'),
	('67619b04-a319-4fb8-b235-0a6c13c7eef8', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_data_interpretation_1769755853579_9t4mn1', 'A', false, 13888, 1, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 14, '2026-01-30 06:51:09.246255+00', 'A class of students voted for their favorite fruit. 25% voted for apples, 35% voted for bananas, 15% voted for grapes, and the rest voted for oranges. What percentage of students voted for oranges?', '{"A": "15%", "B": "20%", "C": "25%", "D": "30%"}', 'C', 'To find the percentage that voted for oranges, subtract the other percentages from 100%: 100% - 25% - 35% - 15% = 25%'),
	('6622c4bc-c7eb-44f6-a04e-95ad61862e3e', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_verbal_reasoning_1769755884657_5z5xsy', 'B', false, 140227, 2, 'verbal_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 16, '2026-01-30 06:53:45.271304+00', 'A baker is to bread as a sculptor is to what?', '{"A": "Oven", "B": "Clay", "C": "Hammer", "D": "Statue"}', 'D', 'A baker creates bread, and a sculptor creates a statue. The relationship is creator to creation.'),
	('68e0f8d9-c9c2-4cc3-8517-52d3cefe92bf', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_verbal_reasoning_1769898304650_otl9rd', 'A', false, 2357, 3, 'verbal_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 3, '2026-01-31 22:26:34.905176+00', 'If all Zogs are Togs and some Togs are Bogs, which statement must be true?', '{"A": "All Zogs are Bogs", "B": "Some Zogs are Bogs", "C": "Some Bogs are Zogs", "D": "No Zogs are Bogs"}', 'B', 'From the premises, it is true that some Zogs are also Bogs'),
	('7388c7aa-2a06-479f-8e47-14d74cd8f91c', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_spatial_reasoning_1769898304650_cnkxb2', 'C', true, 8791, 3, 'spatial_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 4, '2026-01-31 22:26:44.783878+00', 'Rotate the shape clockwise. Which position will the triangle be in after rotation?', '{"A": "Top", "B": "Bottom", "C": "Right", "D": "Left"}', 'C', 'After a clockwise rotation, the triangle will be on the right side'),
	('2f3b9987-0691-4109-839e-3ca7fd8f416c', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769898304650_nxdhoc', 'C', false, 2939, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 7, '2026-01-31 22:27:03.244271+00', 'If A is to B as C is to D, and A=3, B=9, C=4, what is the value of D?', '{"A": "4", "B": "5", "C": "6", "D": "7"}', 'B', 'The ratio between A and B is 1:3, so D must be 3 times C, giving D=12/3=4'),
	('6dc03df6-c82d-46ee-959d-f4f3bfb0d112', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769755595625_2543x7', 'C', false, 1716, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 8, '2026-01-30 06:47:21.788594+00', 'Some cats are black. All black things are cool. Therefore:', '{"A": "All cats are cool.", "B": "Some cats are cool.", "C": "All cool things are cats.", "D": "No cats are cool."}', 'B', 'Since some cats are black, and all black things are cool, it logically follows that some cats are cool.'),
	('d5d44792-df83-4485-8237-42e7b9513944', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_verbal_reasoning_1769755703480_g24mqo', 'B', true, 6191, 1, 'verbal_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 12, '2026-01-30 06:48:30.007448+00', 'Which word best describes someone who always tells the truth?', '{"A": "Dishonest", "B": "Reliable", "C": "Careless", "D": "Greedy"}', 'B', 'Reliable means trustworthy and dependable, which describes someone who always tells the truth.'),
	('1ec75c92-95eb-4f40-9842-8c93a2a107c6', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_logical_reasoning_1769755872141_3nw4md', 'C', true, 9350, 1, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 15, '2026-01-30 06:51:21.820446+00', 'All cats like fish. Ginger is a cat. Therefore, Ginger likes:', '{"A": "Bones", "B": "Milk", "C": "Fish", "D": "Birds"}', 'C', 'Since all cats like fish, and Ginger is a cat, it logically follows that Ginger likes fish.'),
	('90a31da2-8dfd-48b5-9fb6-83fa268453a8', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_spatial_reasoning_1769756037422_48lfwz', 'B', true, 1931, 1, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 18, '2026-01-30 06:53:59.746418+00', 'A square piece of paper is folded in half vertically. Then, it''s folded in half again horizontally. How many layers of paper are there in the final folded shape?', '{"A": "2", "B": "4", "C": "6", "D": "8"}', 'B', 'Folding in half vertically doubles the layers to 2. Folding in half horizontally doubles the layers again to 4.'),
	('6eb780c9-3d68-4bde-a396-fb333117aac8', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d4_numerical_reasoning_1769756111855_wgojea', 'A', true, 14301, 4, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 25, '2026-01-30 06:55:26.524423+00', 'A store is having a sale where all items are 20% off. Sarah buys a jacket originally priced at $65 and a pair of shoes originally priced at $45. If sales tax is 8% of the discounted price, what is the total amount Sarah pays?', '{"A": "$84.24", "B": "$86.40", "C": "$91.80", "D": "$97.20"}', 'A', 'The jacket is $65 * 0.20 = $13 off, so it costs $65 - $13 = $52. The shoes are $45 * 0.20 = $9 off, so they cost $45 - $9 = $36. The total discounted price is $52 + $36 = $88. The sales tax is $88 * 0.08 = $7.04. The total amount Sarah pays is $88 + $7.04 = $95.04.'),
	('b5143621-f48c-448d-acea-9c485d664f1c', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_data_interpretation_1769898304650_bji4p7', 'C', false, 4692, 3, 'data_interpretation', 'diagnostic_screener', 5, '2026-01-31 22:26:50.551724+00', 'If a data set has a mean of 25 and a median of 21, which is true?', '{"A": "The data set has outliers", "B": "The data set is skewed left", "C": "The data set is skewed right", "D": "The data set is normally distributed"}', 'B', 'The mean is higher than the median, indicating a left skew in the data set'),
	('31a48036-6897-47ed-9c34-904e98afe46f', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_diagnostic_d3_logical_reasoning_1769898304650_gazarf', 'B', false, 3190, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'diagnostic_screener', 8, '2026-01-31 22:27:07.523613+00', 'Which word does not belong: Apple, Banana, Orange, Pear, Carrot?', '{"A": "Orange", "B": "Pear", "C": "Banana", "D": "Carrot"}', 'D', 'All options are fruits except Carrot, which is a vegetable'),
	('4657ea51-631a-42f6-a62a-bcffa1f6b4e5', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d1_data_interpretation_1769756031345_ke9le8', 'B', false, 2416, 1, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 17, '2026-01-30 06:53:54.214859+00', 'A class of students recorded their favorite colors. 8 students chose blue, 6 chose red, 4 chose green, and 2 chose yellow. How many students in total were surveyed?', '{"A": "14", "B": "16", "C": "18", "D": "20"}', 'D', 'To find the total number of students, add the number of students who chose each color: 8 + 6 + 4 + 2 = 20.'),
	('2746d778-67da-4764-ac99-599f8514747e', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_verbal_reasoning_1769756042285_l3ahp5', 'C', true, 4056, 2, 'verbal_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 19, '2026-01-30 06:54:06.715473+00', 'A baker is to bread as an artist is to what?', '{"A": "Brush", "B": "Palette", "C": "Painting", "D": "Sculpture"}', 'C', 'A baker creates bread, and an artist creates a painting. While brushes and palettes are tools, and sculpture is a related art form, ''painting'' is the direct product of an artist''s work, analogous to bread for a baker.'),
	('b5bdbef1-e787-4747-96dc-0b4701d36850', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_logical_reasoning_1769756049881_o4kon8', 'A', false, 5727, 3, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 20, '2026-01-30 06:54:15.948807+00', 'All members of the Hiking Club enjoy being outdoors. Some members of the Hiking Club also play soccer. Based on this information, which statement MUST be true?', '{"A": "All people who enjoy being outdoors play soccer.", "B": "Some people who enjoy being outdoors play soccer.", "C": "All people who play soccer enjoy being outdoors.", "D": "No one who enjoys being outdoors plays soccer."}', 'B', 'Since some members of the Hiking Club (who enjoy being outdoors) also play soccer, it must be true that some people who enjoy being outdoors play soccer.'),
	('4a54f6b7-d865-43d5-a8aa-2e2603eb9403', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_verbal_reasoning_1769756059339_9xkyky', 'C', true, 11742, 2, 'verbal_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 21, '2026-01-30 06:54:31.522662+00', 'Complete the analogy: Happy is to Joyful as Sad is to what?', '{"A": "Excited", "B": "Angry", "C": "Miserable", "D": "Content"}', 'C', 'The analogy relates synonyms. ''Miserable'' is a synonym for ''Sad'', just as ''Joyful'' is a synonym for ''Happy''.'),
	('563ddbb6-5b58-4824-9d78-c5806bcbb393', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_spatial_reasoning_1769756074845_g25zn9', 'A', true, 8496, 3, 'spatial_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 22, '2026-01-30 06:54:43.728953+00', 'A rectangular garden is 8 meters long and 6 meters wide. A path of 1 meter width is built around the outside of the garden. What is the area of the path?', '{"A": "28 square meters", "B": "32 square meters", "C": "36 square meters", "D": "40 square meters"}', 'A', 'The outer dimensions of the garden including the path are 10 meters long and 8 meters wide. The total area is 80 square meters. The area of the garden is 48 square meters (8 * 6). Therefore, the area of the path is 80 - 48 = 32 square meters.'),
	('65c557a6-4249-4302-9b82-8764a6093e7d', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d4_pattern_recognition_1769756087469_6lnczy', 'B', true, 9508, 4, 'pattern_recognition', 'adaptive_core', 23, '2026-01-30 06:54:57.319461+00', 'Which of the following shapes logically completes the sequence: Square -> Triangle -> Pentagon -> ______?', '{"A": "Heptagon", "B": "Hexagon", "C": "Octagon", "D": "Decagon"}', 'B', 'The sequence increases the number of sides by 1 each time. A square has 4 sides, a triangle has 3, a pentagon has 5. Therefore, the next shape should have 6 sides, which is a hexagon.'),
	('4a38b880-f75f-46ea-a3eb-6a88f6d81f0c', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d5_logical_reasoning_1769756100688_ajkkg4', 'A', false, 6338, 5, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 24, '2026-01-30 06:55:07.373718+00', 'A detective is investigating a robbery. She knows that either Alice or Bob is the thief, but not both. If Alice is innocent, then the stolen necklace is hidden in the garden. If Bob is innocent, then the necklace is hidden in the attic. The detective searches the garden and does not find the necklace. Who is the thief, and where is the necklace hidden?', '{"A": "Alice is the thief, and the necklace is in the attic.", "B": "Bob is the thief, and the necklace is in the attic.", "C": "Alice is the thief, and the necklace is not found.", "D": "Bob is the thief, and the necklace is not found."}', 'B', 'Since the necklace was not found in the garden, Alice must be the thief. Therefore, Bob is innocent, and the necklace must be hidden in the attic.'),
	('f19b1e33-b8fc-4c03-812f-2566b8d3360e', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d5_data_interpretation_1769756130593_a8ms0p', 'B', false, 6971, 5, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 26, '2026-01-30 06:55:37.885091+00', 'A school''s science club tracked the number of birds visiting their bird feeder each day for a week. The results are: Monday - 15, Tuesday - 22, Wednesday - 18, Thursday - 25, Friday - 20. If the trend of increasing by 7, decreasing by 4, increasing by 7, decreasing by 5 continues on Saturday and Sunday, what will be the total number of birds observed over the entire week?', '{"A": "132", "B": "147", "C": "155", "D": "160"}', 'C', 'The pattern is +7, -4, +7, -5... Following this pattern, Saturday''s count would be 20 + 7 = 27, and Sunday''s count would be 27 - 6 = 21. The total for the week is 15 + 22 + 18 + 25 + 20 + 27 + 28 = 155.'),
	('2552e07d-d33e-4eda-9de5-7443f65cda66', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d4_logical_reasoning_1769756141972_9xanng', 'B', false, 2303, 4, 'logical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 27, '2026-01-30 06:55:44.641256+00', 'A group of friends are deciding what to do on Saturday. If it rains, they will go to the movies. If it is sunny, they will go to the park. If the weather is cloudy, they will play board games at home. On Saturday, they ended up baking cookies. Which of the following statements is most likely true?', '{"A": "It rained on Saturday.", "B": "It was sunny on Saturday.", "C": "The weather forecast was incorrect.", "D": "Someone suggested a different activity."}', 'D', 'Since they ended up baking cookies, an activity not directly related to the initial weather-dependent plans, it is most likely that someone suggested a different activity that everyone agreed to.'),
	('d64175ca-fb99-464c-a555-7ab50b5838a1', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_core_d2_numerical_reasoning_1769898435696_iyxej2', 'B', true, 3460, 2, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 9, '2026-01-31 22:27:19.6647+00', 'If x=3 and y=5, what is the value of 2x + 3y?', '{"A": "13", "B": "19", "C": "23", "D": "29"}', 'B', '2(3) + 3(5) = 6 + 15 = 21'),
	('3657cfde-315b-4aa9-ad34-025a8a4a6de1', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_adaptive_core_d3_data_interpretation_1769898442693_7tpxev', 'A', false, 4173, 3, 'data_interpretation', 'adaptive_core', 10, '2026-01-31 22:27:27.316621+00', 'In a survey, 40% of people prefer tea, 30% prefer coffee, and the rest prefer juice. If 120 people were surveyed, how many prefer juice?', '{"A": "30", "B": "40", "C": "45", "D": "50"}', 'C', 'The percentage of people who prefer juice is 100% - 40% - 30% = 30%. 30% of 120 is 36 people, so 36 people prefer juice.'),
	('9e690afd-92be-4fa6-80a3-b620671dfb24', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d3_numerical_reasoning_1769756147313_qiaxh0', 'C', false, 2428, 3, 'numerical_reasoning', 'adaptive_core', 28, '2026-01-30 06:55:50.119346+00', 'A bakery sells cupcakes for $3 each and cookies for $1.50 each. Sarah buys 5 cupcakes and 8 cookies. How much does she spend in total?', '{"A": "$25.50", "B": "$27.00", "C": "$28.50", "D": "$30.00"}', 'B', 'The cupcakes cost 5 * $3 = $15. The cookies cost 8 * $1.50 = $12. The total cost is $15 + $12 = $27.'),
	('b00c6ec5-dab1-436b-83bb-f037c05616de', 'd25e061d-4948-4d21-897e-df97a39815ca', 'middle_school_adaptive_core_d2_pattern_recognition_1769756152721_crurb2', 'B', true, 10772, 2, 'pattern_recognition', 'adaptive_core', 29, '2026-01-30 06:56:03.943183+00', 'What number comes next in this sequence: 3, 8, 13, 18, ?', '{"A": "22", "B": "23", "C": "24", "D": "25"}', 'B', 'The sequence increases by 5 each time. 18 + 5 = 23.'),
	('0456c5f1-0c6b-4475-8e9b-44a8243e27e9', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_stability_dundefined_numerical_reasoning_1769898453577_roqw5o', 'C', false, 3574, 2, 'numerical_reasoning', 'stability_confirmation', 11, '2026-01-31 22:27:37.621874+00', 'If a triangle has angles measuring 60°, 70°, and 50°, what is the measure of the remaining angle?', '{"A": "40°", "B": "50°", "C": "60°", "D": "70°"}', 'A', 'The sum of angles in a triangle is always 180°. So, the remaining angle would be 180° - 60° - 70° = 50°.'),
	('b6fb4a23-29d9-4b44-beed-74e34c117847', '46eeaacd-c441-48ae-aedc-61ce30c151d0', 'higher_secondary_stability_dundefined_data_interpretation_1769898453577_vl6az6', 'B', false, 2940, 2, 'data_interpretation', 'stability_confirmation', 15, '2026-01-31 22:27:52.790733+00', 'If A + B = 10 and A - B = 4, what is the value of A?', '{"A": "7", "B": "6", "C": "5", "D": "4"}', 'A', 'Solving the equations simultaneously gives A=7 and B=3. Therefore, A=7.');


